result.execSummary:
The defendant Jennings Christian Putnam was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jennings Christian Putnam is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jennings Christian Putnam was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Michael Edward Nieskes, DF ATTY: Daniel Frank Demaio, DF: Jennings Christian Putnam appeared.  Court called at 3:37 p.m.  Includes case 15CF442, 15CM488, 15TR3995, 15TR3996 & 15TR3997.   Set for Plea/sentencing.  There is an agreement.  State moves to amend Ct. 1 in 15CF442 to 346.62(2) (Wreckless Driving).  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads Guilty to the amended Ct 1 in 346.62(2) (Wreckless Driving). in 15CF442.  DE pleads Guilty to Ct. 1 in 15CM488.  DE pleads Guilty to Ct. 1 in 15TR3995 (OWI 1st).  Court reviews the police reports.   Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds the DE adjudicated guilty of the amended Ct 1 346.62(2) in 15CF442 & Ct. 1 in 15CM488 and Ct. 1 in 15TR3995. On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 2 in 15CM488 & 15TR3996 & 15TR3997. Sentencing arguments. Crt orders:

Ct. 1 (346.62(2) (Wreckless Driving)
F/F $389.50  
- DE to meet with the payment clerk for a payment plan

 Ct. 1 15CM488
- Restitution in the amount of $2,020 to be paid to the Houlton Elementary School
- Money on the file to pay the restitution first before being applied to the attorney fees
- Court costs in the amount of $243 .00 and $200.00 for the DNA sample
- DE to meet with the payment clerk for a payment plan
- DE to go downstairs to the jail to give a DNA sample

- Ct. 1 15TR3995 (OWI 1st)
- AODA and follow through with any recommended treatment or therapy
- 6 months drivers license revocation
- F/F of $811.50 
- DE to meet with the payment clerk for a payment plan

- 20 days to appeal
